create index <index_name> on <table_name> ( <column1>, <column2>, â€¦ );

primary indexes are created with primary key and only that column.
Oracle creates indexes on primary key by default.

Composite indexes are cretaed with more than one column.

Query optimizer decides if it can user the indexes : 
A SQL statement can be executed in many different ways, such as full table scans, index scans, nested loops, and hash joins. 
The query optimizer determines the most efficient way to execute a SQL statement after considering many factors related 
to the objects referenced and the conditions specified in the query. 
This determination is an important step in the processing of any SQL statement and can greatly affect execution time.
